Reference code/provenance for the `pda_brexit` benchmark.

  Fun/L2relax.R   The authors' L2-relaxation function, vendored verbatim from
                  github.com/ishwang1/L2relax-PDA (folder Fun/). Included for
                  provenance only -- a single function so a reader can see the
                  exact program the Python reference reproduces. (The multiple-
                  treated aggregation in PDA.multitreat.R is reproduced by
                  mlsynth's run_pda_multitreat; the per-firm fit is L2relax.R.)
  reference.py    A faithful port of Fun/L2relax.R's convex program, solved with
                  cvxpy per UK firm. It standardises the treated-firm/control
                  pre-period series exactly as the R function (intercept=TRUE,
                  standardize=TRUE) with a SHARED control Sigma = X'X/T1 and a
                  per-firm eta = X'y/T1, minimises ||beta||^2 subject to
                  |eta - Sigma beta| <= tau elementwise, then de-standardises.
                  It reads the same basedata/brexit_long.parquet that mlsynth
                  fits.

License / redistribution
  The L2relax-PDA repository ships NO explicit license file (checked: no
